    playingStyle: `Brinkman is a penalty area specialist — a forward who generates most of his goals from inside the opposition's shooting circle rather than from long-range efforts. He is ambidextrous with his stick, capable of finishing from both the forehand and backhand side, which makes him exceptionally difficult to defend in one-on-one situations inside the circle.\n\nHis off-the-ball movement is elite: he pins defenders with runs that drag them away from their structure, creating space for midfielders like Florent Van Aubel to arrive late into dangerous positions. In the 2025-26 Pro League, Brinkman topped the scoring charts with 18 goals in 16 matches.`,
