    worldCupPreview: `Netherlands are among the top three favourites to win the 2026 World Cup alongside Belgium and Australia. In Pool A, they face Argentina, Spain, and South Africa — a group they are expected to top comfortably. But the deeper knockout rounds will test Brinkman against defences specifically set up to contain him.\n\nA potential Quarter-Final against Pool B runners-up (possibly Germany or France) is where Brinkman's ability to operate in tight spaces will be decisive. Netherlands' system — a high-press 4-3-3 — gives Brinkman licence to press from the front, winning turnovers high up the pitch that directly create scoring opportunities.`,
    careerMilestones: `112 caps, 67 goals. Olympic silver medal (2020 Tokyo). FIH Pro League top scorer 2025-26. Champions Trophy winner 2023. HC Amsterdam's all-time top scorer in a single season (2024-25, Dutch Hoofdklasse). Named in FIH World XI for 2025.`,
